{"questionId":"13927449","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The computer then selects at random an integer <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math>, inclusive. Each outcome is equally likely.</p>\n<p>Daniel is trying to determine the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> and asks if <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn></math>. He is told that it is not <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Alessia asks if <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> is odd. Show that her expected information gained is greater than Daniel’s expected information gained.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mfenced><mi>I</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>693</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>693147</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>693</mn><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>325</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13927449","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.2cii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Alessia asks if x is odd. Show that her expected information gained is greater than Daniel’s expected information gained.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.7—Discrete random variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
